OL,3,CCalls for care home 'top up fees'
OL,4,Creform
OL,6,FReport by Gareth Wilkinson,
OL,7,FCorrespondent
OL,9,FCampaigners and families say that the
OL,10,Fsystem of third party or top up fees
OL,11,Ffor residential and nursing care for
OL,12,Fthe elderly needs to be reformed and
OL,13,Fneeds clarity.
OL,15,FEach health trust has what they call
OL,16,Fis the regional rate or an average
OL,17,Fspend that it will pay for a person's
OL,18,Fassessed care needs but if a nursing
OL,19,For residential home costs more than
OL,20,Fthat rate, then a third party like a
OL,21,Ffamily member can pay the difference.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/16
