OL,3,CCalls for care home 'top up fees'
OL,4,Creform
OL,6,FFor Margaret Bradley the financial
OL,7,Fburden became too much after the top
OL,8,Fup fee for her mother's care almost
OL,9,Fdoubled. Although she was afraid to
OL,10,Fmake a fuss and risk jeopardising her
OL,11,Fmother's care, she questioned why she
OL,12,Fwas incurring the extra charge. After
OL,13,Ffailing to get a clear answer, and
OL,14,Fwhile battling cancer herself, she
OL,15,Fstopped paying. While a bill of
OL,16,Fseveral hundred pounds did mount up,
OL,17,Fafter the intervention of her local
OL,18,FMLA, she was told she no longer had to
OL,19,Fpay.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/16
