OL,3,CCalls for care home 'top up fees'
OL,4,Creform
OL,6,FIn a statement the Department of
OL,7,FHealth told UTV that top up fees are
OL,8,Fset by the independent care home
OL,9,Fprovider at a level they deem
OL,10,Fappropriate to reflect market prices.
OL,11,FIt says that neither the Department of
OL,12,FHealth, nor the Health and Social Care
OL,13,FTrusts, have any role in setting or
OL,14,Fcalculating these fees.
OL,16,FIt also adds that top up fees are
OL,17,Fdefined as additional payments made
OL,18,Fwhen a resident or their family
OL,19,Fchooses a care home placement that is
OL,20,Fmore expensive than the standard rate
OL,21,Ffunded by the HSC Trust.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/16
