OL,3,CCalls for care home 'top up fees'
OL,4,Creform
OL,6,FHowever, when Michael Hogg was told
OL,7,Fhis mother needed nursing care after
OL,8,Fbeing admitted to hospital, he says he
OL,9,Fmade it clear from the outset that he
OL,10,Fwould not pay top up fees without
OL,11,Fclarity about what they were for. He
OL,12,Fsays that refusal meant that Elinor,
OL,13,Fwho suffers from advanced dementia,
OL,14,Fspent almost a year in Craigavon
OL,15,FHospital before a suitable facility
OL,16,Fwas found. He is calling for reform of
OL,17,Fthe top-up fees system so that
OL,18,Ffamilies and third parties understand
OL,19,Fexactly what they are paying for.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
